message.content:
Bombus impatiens, also known as the common eastern bumblebee, is a species of bumblebee found in North America.

This species has a fuzzy black and yellow banded body with a roundish shape.

The size of a Bombus impatiens is typically smaller than other bumblebee species.

Their abdomen is black and has a stinger at the end.

The workers have a black head while the males have a yellow patch on their head.

Bombus impatiens can be found in fields, gardens, and other areas with a variety of flowering plants.

The bumblebee plays an important role in pollinating plants and the species is common in agriculture.
